# .cursorrules — production-rag-eval
# Owner: Sebastien Henry. Anchor: Anthropic Claude for FS / Harvey / Databricks.
# Benchmark: FinanceBench (PatronusAI/financebench) — public, 150 Q&A, real 10-Ks.

You are pairing with a senior AI engineer. Write production code. No tutorials.

## Stack (pinned Jun 2026)
- Python 3.12.4. uv 0.5.x. ruff 0.8.4. mypy 1.13 --strict. pydantic 2.9.
- anthropic==0.40.0. Claude Sonnet 4.6 for generation, Haiku for contextualization.
- cohere==5.13.4 (rerank-v3.5 only — no Cohere generation).
- voyageai==0.3.2 (voyage-3-large, output_dimension=256, Matryoshka).
- qdrant-client==1.12.1 for dense vector storage.
- rank-bm25==0.2.2 for lexical retrieval.
- ragas==0.2.12, deepeval==2.4.1, scipy==1.14.1 for evals.
- FastAPI 0.115.6, httpx 0.28.1 async. structlog 24.4.0.

## Architecture invariants
- Pipeline: ingest -> chunk -> contextualize -> index -> [query time] ->
  bm25_retrieve -> dense_retrieve -> rrf_fuse -> cohere_rerank ->
  conformal_abstention -> generate_with_citations -> evaluate.
- Contextual Retrieval: every chunk gets a 1-2 sentence context prefix
  generated by Claude Haiku before embedding. Context prefix is NOT indexed
  separately — it is prepended to the chunk text before embedding + BM25 index.
- Conformal abstention: calibrated on data/calibration/calib_split.jsonl (120 Qs).
  Nonconformity score = 1 - (max_rerank_score). Threshold tau at
  (1-alpha)(1+1/n) quantile of calibration scores, alpha=0.10.
  At inference: if nonconformity_score > tau -> abstain with
  {"abstained": True, "reason": "insufficient_retrieval_confidence"}.
- Citations: every CitedAnswer must include >= 2 CitedSpan objects with
  char offsets into the source passage. CitationContractError if < 2.
- Eval: all four eval metrics (ragas_faithfulness, hhem_score,
  deepeval_score, citation_coverage) computed and stored per run.
  CI gate: ragas_faithfulness >= 0.85, citation_coverage = 1.00.

## Forbidden patterns
- Generating answers without going through conformal_abstention — always check.
- Embedding chunks without the Contextual Retrieval prefix.
- LLM calls in the retrieval path (retrieval is always lexical + dense + rerank).
- Mutable global state (Qdrant client, BM25 index) — always dependency-injected.
- Fabricated eval numbers in README — run the eval, copy the output.
- print() in src/ — structlog only.

## Eval honesty contract
- README eval table must be generated from the most recent evals/runs/*/summary.json.
- Never manually edit eval numbers.
- Abstention rate must be reported alongside accuracy metrics.
  Formula: answered_correctly / (n_answered + n_abstained).
  Separately: abstention_rate = n_abstained / n_total.
- If a metric is NOT yet computed (e.g., HHEM requires local model), mark as "pending".
